values:
Well...it's almost 10:30 in the morning.  I didn't have to give Sami a bath (she didn't have any nasty stuff on her, but she smells slightly), she'll definately get one tonight though.  I'm hoping to find that brochure I got from the Earth Day vendor I bought soap for Sami from.  We are out and it really did take the smell(s) off her skin.  First time I'd found something that could do that no matter what mess Sami got into.  
Haven't heard or seen the landlord yet.  Hope the pump gets fixed today.  Would really like a shower.  Not to mention I'm not looking forward to having to heat water up and carry it in the bathroom for the kids to have a bath.  Man...I'm glad we have indoor plumbing!  I'm not sure how the ladies did it back when there wasn't any!
Well...not much else going on.  Feeling a bit tired today...and I shouldn't.  I'm hungry and I shouldn't be...so I guess I'll go make me a snack and take a nap.  The kids won't be off the buses for a couple hours yet.

BOY
 He's upside down and backwards but was kind enough not to close his legs! :) Will name him Dominik Thomas...and NO B...I WILL NOT NAME HIM TAD!!! :) He's currently 15 ounces in weight and I'm 21 weeks if anyone is interested.:) Still have a lot of months to go through with hot, muggy, and more than likely uncomfortable weather. Doctor was called into the ultrasound because of old scar tissue...which showed up in the ultrasound and everyone wanted to make sure that's what it was. Had a pelvic...what fun *sigh*, talked to my doctor about the glucose machine...got my levels changed (numbers to acheive) and still have to check at least 4 times a day. Will need to check an hour after I eat though instead of before I eat and still check when I get up in the mornings. Since I've not being doing this the past week...got to get back with the program. The bit of good news on this front was Dr. Smith said if I checked my blood and levels were within range for an entire day...then the next day I could check it a couple times instead:D Yippee... Think I called everyone I was suppose to about the appointment and if not I'm sure I'll hear from them eventually. Came home, tried calling my supervisor to find out what happened during the conference call I missed (doctor's appointment) and had to leave a message. Hope to hear from her soon. I'm gonna try again when I get off here... Took an hour and a half nap before John got home. Let John read the "it's a boy" words on the ultrasound picture and he started grinning from ear to ear. When I asked him if he understood what that meant he said "YEP...I'm gonna have a baby brother" and continued to grin...lol John has asked several times if he can feel when the baby moves. I'm not sure John would be able to tell at this stage...but told him I'd let him try next time Dominik started kicking me. Well...that's about it for now. Got a lot going on some good some bad and at the moment...I don't want to share the bad.

I've spent most of the afternoon and evening with a friend.  Stay with me on this...one of her close girlfriends lost her baby.  She asked my friend to watch her youngest (10-month old) while she went to the doctor.  I went to my friends house to help her keep her sanity...the baby was a screamer.  And had a nice healthy set of lungs on him.  I was there when she got the news from her friend that she'd lost her baby.  She was 30 weeks...that's 7 1/2 months.  My friend took it hard.  I know this woman through my friend and I felt deep empathy.  I still feel very sad for this woman.  They new the baby was going to be a girl...and this woman wanted a little girl so badly (she has four sons).  My friend feels a guilty because she has girls.  I understand what she's going through.

I brought her home with me.  We fixed dinner, talked, and began watching a movie.  Waiting for her husband to come and pick her up.  I'm glad she won't be alone tonight.  I hope she knows she only needs to call and I'm here for her.

I'm sad.  Makes me rub my tummy and think of the four weeks I went through of uncertainty.  Not sure how I'd handle it if I lost the baby that far into my pregnancy.  I pray God is helping this woman any way she needs.  You good thoughts and prayers are appriecated.

Night.

The day started ok.  Got the kids up and off to school.  Then ran my mom over to Blountstown cause her van broke down.  We had breakfast and I ran her to do a few errands.  Wasn't as bad as I thought it would be.  Ended up getting home and taking a three hour nap.  Not sure what's wrong with me...seem to want to sleep more and more lately.  Starting to woner if I'm getting enough nutrition.  Anywhoo....

Took the kids over to D&A's so I could come back and get ready for dinner.  Ended up chatting for a bit and getting a bookcase type thing;)  Left the house a little late but still got to T&H's by 6:15.  We were suppose to be at the place by 7:15...or at least that was the plan ;)  We got stuck behind a train that was crossing...lol so Viv and Westley beat us there.  They let them know we were there and and waited for us to arrive.  WOW ... even with call ahead reservations...we ended up waiting an hour.  Wasn't to bad.  Got to chat and get to know Westley and Viv a little more.  I got a little monkey from them...it's so dang cute!

Dinner was wonderful!  Although...next time I'm gonna order desert first like I teased I was gonna.  Wow...I got full fast.:)  Oh well...I got to bring home most of my steak and John and I will probably share it tomorrow.

Picked up the kids from D and came home.  Got the kids ready for bed, tucked in, and then I crashed.
